        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:06PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 406 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Lincolnton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Lincolnton, Shelby, Cherryville, Bessemer City, Dallas,
Stanley, Ranlo, High Shoals, and Waco.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
